The paper discusses signal processing techniques for millimeter wave MIMO systems, which are primarily related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges faced by using MIMO communication at higher carrier frequencies, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the applications of mmWave in vehicular area networks, ad hoc networks, and wearables, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and augmented reality (cs.AR).
